# Question 2 - Secure Project Workspace Setup

## Command 1
$ mkdir -p ~/CLI-Graded-Assignment/Q2
$ cd ~/CLI-Graded-Assignment/Q2

Explanation: Created the Q2 working directory and moved into it.

## Command 2
$ mkdir -p ProjectWorkspace/Documents ProjectWorkspace/Reports

Explanation: Created the workspace folder with two subfolders, Documents and Reports.

## Command 3
$ ls -R ProjectWorkspace
ProjectWorkspace:
Documents  Reports

ProjectWorkspace/Documents:

ProjectWorkspace/Reports:

Explanation: Listed the workspace structure recursively, confirming the two subfolders were created.

## Command 4
$ ls -ld ProjectWorkspace
drwxr-xr-x 4 coder coder 4 Jun 23 11:45 ProjectWorkspace

Explanation: Showed the permissions before modification. By default the owner has full access while group and others can read and enter.

## Command 5
$ chmod 700 ProjectWorkspace

Explanation: Changed permissions so that only the owner has access. The 7 gives the owner read, write, and execute, and the two zeros remove all access for group and others.

## Command 6
$ ls -ld ProjectWorkspace
drwx------ 4 coder coder 4 Jun 23 11:45 ProjectWorkspace

Explanation: Showed the permissions after modification. The folder is now drwx------, meaning only the owner can access it.

## Command 7
$ umask
0022

Explanation: Displayed the default permission mask. 0022 removes write permission for group and others on newly created files and folders.
